    *   `system`:  Set to "Hematology".
    *   `topic`: Set to "Lymphomas".
    *   `difficulty`:  A string representing the difficulty level ("E", "M", or "D").
    *   `front`: The question or keyword displayed on the front of the flashcard.
    *   `back`: An object containing the following properties:
        *   `definition`: The definition or short answer.
        *   `high\_yield`: A high-yield summary point.
        *   `clinical\_pearl`: A clinical pearl or relevant fact.
*   **ES Module Export:** The `export default lymphomasFlashcards;` line makes the `lymphomasFlashcards` array available for use in other parts of your React Native application.

